<paragraph id="25262F0E103DFFA2DBB2FC974FBC2F4F" blockId="24.[151,1437,987,1122]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
A good number of females and males of 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D103DFFA2D97EFC974ED128D8" authority="Okajima, 2006" box="[603,740,987,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C103DFFA2D97EFC974ED128D8" box="[603,740,987,1014]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been known from Southern 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103DFFA2DF78FC9748A828DB" box="[1117,1181,988,1014]" name="Japan" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Ishigaki and Iriomote Islands, the Ryukyus) and 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E103DFFA2DAF1FCB44E1C2F34" box="[468,553,1023,1049]" name="Taiwan" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and both macropterous and micropterous forms are known in both sexes. Bicolourous abdomen of this species is unique in the genus. The fifth to eighth adominal segments are somewhat yellowish in contrast with brown anterior segments (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B103DFFA2D9C1FB0C4F4E2F4F" box="[740,891,1095,1122]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 17 &amp; 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
